<li><a href="http://www.aef.com/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.aef.com/index.html" rel="nofollow">Advertising Educational Foundation</a>, archived advertising exhibits and classroom resources</li>
<li><a href="http://liinwww.ira.uka.de/bibliography/Ai/web-advertising.html" class="external text" title="http://liinwww.ira.uka.de/bibliography/Ai/web-advertising.html" rel="nofollow">Bibliography on Web Advertising</a></li>
<li><a href="http://library.duke.edu/digitalcollections/adaccess/" class="external text" title="http://library.duke.edu/digitalcollections/adaccess/" rel="nofollow">Ad*Access -- Duke University Libraries Digital Collections</a> Over 7,000 U.S. and Canadian advertisements, dated 1911-1955, covering five product categories - Beauty and Hygiene, Radio, Television, Transportation, and World War II propaganda.</li>
<li><a href="http://library.duke.edu/digitalcollections/eaa/" class="external text" title="http://library.duke.edu/digitalcollections/eaa/" rel="nofollow">Emergence of Advertising in America -- Duke University Libraries Digital Collections -</a> Includes 9,000 advertising items and publications dating from 1850 to 1920, illustrating the rise of consumer culture and the birth of a professionalized advertising industry in the United States.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.eisnermuseum.org/exhibits/online.shtm" class="external text" title="http://www.eisnermuseum.org/exhibits/online.shtm" rel="nofollow">On-Line exhibits</a> at <a href="http://www.eisnermuseum.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.eisnermuseum.org/" rel="nofollow">William F. Eisner Museum of Advertising and Design</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.aaaindia.org" class="external text" title="http://www.aaaindia.org" rel="nofollow">Advertising Agencies Association of India - AAAI</a> AAAI GoaFest 2009 <a href="http://www.resorts-in-goa.com/aaai-goafest-2009.php" class="external text" title="http://www.resorts-in-goa.com/aaai-goafest-2009.php" rel="nofollow">Accommodation in South Goa for GoaFest 2009</a></li>
